                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=nomadhacker",
                        "name": "nomadhacker",
                        "displayName": "Michael Stubblefield",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I strongly agree.  One of the selling points of Zend is that you're supposed to be able to use the library without having to use their model, or use it within existing applications.  \r\n\r\nWhy does a PHP notice get turned into an exception?  Why can't Zend just use an existing session like PHP core language itself does?  \r\n\r\nEven a configuration option to use an existing session would be an improvement.",
